§ Why ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ The set of positive semidefinite matrices turns out to be a
    cone in the vector space of $n × n$ matrices. ⦉
⦉

§ Main result ⦉
<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ $𝗦_+^d$ is a convex, pointed, closed cone with interior
    $𝗦_{++}^d$ relative to $𝗦^d$.
    † ⦊
      ‖ Future editions will contain a proof. ⦉
    ⦉⦉
</statement>
¶ ⦊
  ‖ The cone of positive definite matrices is open. ⦉
⦉

